# UI And Theme

- Use Ant Design 5 components and project wrappers for common UI patterns.
- Layout should stay consistent with `AppLayout`, `Header`, and `Sider`.
- `themeMode` lives in `configSlice`; `App.tsx` switches Ant Design `defaultAlgorithm` and `darkAlgorithm`.
- App-level colors must use CSS variables from `src/index.css`.
- When adding app-level colors, define both `:root` and `[data-theme='dark']` values.
- Avoid hardcoded brand/trademark colors or third-party logos.
- Make new UI readable in both light and dark modes.
- Prefer Ant Design tokens and props before custom CSS.
